model

Class Profile

  • java.lang.Object
    • model.Profile
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    Admin, User

    public abstract class Profile
extends java.lang.Object
    Abstract base class representing a user profile in the system. This class defines the common attributes and behavior shared by all types of user profiles, including both regular users and administrators. Profile serves as the foundation for user identity management and provides the core personal information storage and retrieval functionality for the application.

    • Constructor Detail

      • Profile

        public Profile()
        Default constructor that initializes all profile attributes to empty values. The ID is set to -1 to indicate an unpersisted profile that hasn't been assigned a database identifier yet.

      • Profile

               java.lang.String p_name,
               java.lang.String p_lastname,
               java.lang.String p_telephone)
        Constructs a Profile with all attributes including the database ID. This constructor is typically used when loading existing profile data from persistent storage where the ID has already been assigned.
        Parameters:
        p_id - the unique identifier for the profile
        p_email - the email address associated with the profile
        p_username - the username used for authentication
        p_password - the password used for authentication
        p_name - the first name of the profile owner
        p_lastname - the last name of the profile owner
        p_telephone - the telephone number of the profile owner
